| **Platform** | Odoo.sh (SaaS/PaaS) |

## SSH Access

```bash
ssh 30217068@cryptoxdog-ib-odoo-19-staging-30217068.dev.odoo.com
```

- Build number `30217068` is the SSH username
- Host is the full Odoo.sh dev domain
- No port override needed (default 22)
- SSH key must be registered in Odoo.sh project settings

## Shell Commands (Once Connected)

```bash
# Odoo shell (Python REPL with ORM)
odoo-bin shell -d <dbname>

# View logs
cat ~/logs/odoo.log
tail -f ~/logs/odoo.log

# Update a module
odoo-bin -u plasticos_base --stop-after-init

# Install a module
odoo-bin -i plasticos_new_module --stop-after-init
```

## Web Lead API Endpoints (Staging)

| Method | Path | Auth |
|--------|------|------|
| `POST` | `/api/v1/web-lead` | Bearer token |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/cognito-webhook` | Bearer token |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/web-lead/health` | None |

## Important Notes

- Pushing to the `Staging` branch triggers automatic deployment on Odoo.sh
- `git push` to Staging = live deployment (see `01-git-push-prohibition.mdc`)
- SSH sessions are ephemeral — file changes outside the Odoo filestore are lost on rebuild
- Database name may differ from branch name; check with `odoo-bin shell` or Odoo.sh dashboard
